KW  - Closed-end fund
KW  - Open-end fund
KW  - Mutual fund
KW  - Organizational form
AB  - We investigate the choice of organizational form for investment funds. We find that funds that hold less liquid securities with less transparent prices are more likely to be closed-end. The relation is economically meaningful as well as statistically significant. Our results are consistent with Fama and Jensen's [J. Law Econ. 26 (1983a) 327; J. Law Econ. 26 (1983b) 301] prediction that redeemable shares are not efficient when assets are relatively illiquid and asset prices are difficult to observe.
